When bit n in direction is set to 1, port n drives out the value in the corresponding bit of the data register The direction register only exists when the PIO core hardware is configured in bidirectional mode. The mode (input, output, or bidirectional) is specified at system generation time, and cannot be changed at runtime. In input-only or output-only mode, the direction register does not exist.
